# Rust Conventions

## Style

- Edition 2021, MSRV 1.85
- Prefer `thiserror` for library errors, `anyhow` at binary edges
- Async: Tokio only; no blocking I/O on async paths
- Keep modules focused — one concern per file

## Patterns

```rust
// ✅ Guard before DB
let prepared = validate_and_prepare(sql, engine, write_mode, max_rows)?;
// then execute

// ❌ Execute then validate
```

```rust
// ✅ Columnar result
ColumnarResult { cols, rows, meta }

// ❌ Vec<HashMap<String, Value>> row objects
```

## sqlx

- Use `EnginePool` enum — never leak raw Pg/MySQL types into tools
- Timeouts via `tokio::time::timeout`
- Pool size from CLI (`--pool-size`)

## rmcp tools

- Short `#[tool(description = "...")]` — tokens cost every turn
- Params via `Parameters<T>` + `schemars::JsonSchema`
- Filter tools in `list_tools` when `!full_tools`

## Tests

- Guard tests: no DB required
- Prefer unit tests in-module + `tests/unit.rs`
- Name: `blocks_*`, `allows_*`, `truncates_*`
